1. Go to prometheus docs, read the isntallation guide
2. download prometheus, extract it 
3. cp the prometheus executable to /usr/local/bin 
4. try to run prometheus --help from your home directory


To disaply your path env var => echo $PATH

Task2:
Follow the instructions page 32-35 in the slides to configure prometheus as systemd service 
(Home Task) => Do it using Ansible

Task3:
Install prometheus using Docker ( K8S bouns ), make sure to mount both config file and the database 
https://prometheus.io/docs/prometheus/latest/installation/

Please learn python basics, we will need it in the instrumentation



